{% extends 'layouts/page.njk' %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">{{ heading }}</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <div class="govuk-body" data-testid="app-page-body">
        <p class="govuk-body-l">
          An AI‑powered content review tool that helps ensure your content meets GOV.UK standards.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What this tool does</h2>
        <p>The Content Review Tool helps you:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Review content for plain English and GOV.UK style compliance</li>
          <li>Check plain text against key GOV.UK style guidelines</li>
          <li>Identify areas for improvement in readability</li>
          <li>Get AI-powered suggestions for better content</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How to use this tool</h2>
        <p>There are three ways to submit content for review:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li><strong>Paste or type text</strong> — enter your content directly in the text area on the home page</li>
          <li><strong>Paste a GOV.UK URL</strong> — paste the URL of any GOV.UK page and the tool will automatically extract the page text for review</li>
          <li><strong>Upload a document</strong> — upload a PDF or Word document and the tool will automatically extract the body text for review. If present, table of contents is excluded from review</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The AI will review the content against GOV.UK standards and provide detailed feedback.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Text input requirements</h3>
        <p>Your content must be:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Up to <strong>100,000 characters</strong> long (minimum 10 characters)</li>
          <li>Plain text (the AI cannot review formatting like bold text, headings or links)</li>
          <li>In English</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          <p><strong>Tip:</strong> For best results, submit one section or page of content at a time rather than very long documents.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Processing time</h2>
        <p>Reviews are typically completed within 30 seconds to 2 minutes. Processing time may vary depending on:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>content length and complexity</li>
          <li>current service demand</li>
          <li>analysis depth required</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>The page will automatically update when your review is ready. You can also close the page and come back later, your review will still be waiting for you in the review history.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Error handling and retry mechanism</h2>
        <p>In the event of temporary service interruptions, the system will automatically retry your review request without requiring user intervention. This ensures reliable processing even during periods of high demand or brief service unavailability.</p>
        
        <p>Should a review fail after multiple automated retry attempts, an error notification will be displayed. In such cases, please resubmit your content for review.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How the AI reviews your content</h2>
        <p>The AI evaluates your content against 2 key categories:</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">1. Plain English</h3>
        <p>The AI checks for:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Use of clear, simple language</li>
          <li>Complex words that could be simplified</li>
          <li>Sentence length (aiming for 15-20 words average)</li>
          <li>Spelling and grammar errors</li>
          <li>Content not written in British English</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2. GOV.UK Style Compliance</h3>
        <p>The AI checks for:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Passive voice usage (active voice is preferred)</li>
          <li>Common GOV.UK "words to avoid" (e.g., "utilise", "facilitate", "going forward"), abbreviations and acronyms</li>
          <li>Adherence to key GOV.UK style guidelines for language, capitalisation, punctuation, contractions, emails and links</li>
          <li>Correct use of numerals vs words (e.g., "9am", not "nine o'clock"), dates and times</li>
          <li>Use of "please" (GOV.UK style is direct and instructional, not deferential)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          <p><strong>Note:</strong> The AI reviews plain text only. It cannot evaluate visual formatting elements like headings, lists, or links. Focus is on language quality.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Review output</h2>
        <p>After reviewing your content, the AI provides:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>A summary with scores for each of the 2 categories</li>
          <li>Your original content with highlighted areas for improvement</li>
          <li>List of improvements with examples and suggestions</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          <p><strong>Note:</strong> Reviews older than 5 days are automatically deleted from the system.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Content quality indicators</h2>

        <p><strong>Good Content (Score: 4–5)</strong></p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Written in plain English with short, clear sentences (under 25 words)</li>
          <li>Active voice used throughout, no complex language</li>
          <li>Follows key GOV.UK style guidelines (e.g., numerals, date formats, capitalisation)</li>
          <li>No common GOV.UK "words-to-avoid" used (e.g., "utilise", "facilitate", "leverage")</li>
          <li>Accurate abbreviation and acronym usage on first reference</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Average Content (Score: 2–3)</strong></p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Mix of simple and complex language; some sentences exceed 25 words</li>
          <li>Some passive voice constructions present</li>
          <li>Partially follows GOV.UK style with minor inconsistencies</li>
          <li>Occasional use of GOV.UK "words-to-avoid"</li>
          <li>Minor capitalisation, number, or date formatting issues</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Poor Content (Score: 1)</strong></p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Heavy use of complex language and phrasing throughout</li>
          <li>Long, convoluted sentences that are difficult to follow</li>
          <li>Widespread use of GOV.UK "words-to-avoid" and passive voice</li>
          <li>Text content would not meet the standard required for GOV.UK publication</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Important information about AI suggestions</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">AI review suggestions are <strong>advisory only</strong>. They are generated solely from the content you submit and the service's predefined review criteria. You should use your own judgement when deciding whether to act on any suggestion.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Your submitted content is <strong>not</strong> used to train, fine-tune or improve the AI model in any way.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Before your content is processed, it is automatically scanned and any personally identifiable information (PII) is redacted. Submissions containing sensitive information cannot be processed.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Access and sign-in</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">You must sign in using your Defra Microsoft account (Azure Active Directory). Users outside the Defra AAD tenant cannot access this service.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Your session will automatically end after <strong>1 hour of inactivity</strong>. Sign-in events and service activity are logged in OpenSearch dashboards for monitoring and security purposes. Application logs are retained for <strong>6 weeks</strong> in OpenSearch and are also archived to AWS S3.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

{% endblock %}
